<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>hang in the bell-ropes • hang on the bell</xh5><p> <i>hang in the bell-ropes</i>—(UK arch.) said of a postponed marriage: During the currency of the three Sundays on which the banns were proclaimed the young couple were said jocosely to be “<u>hanging in the bell-ropes</u>.”</p><p> <i>hang on the bell—</i>ring the doorbell over and over again: I want to see mountains again. And then find somewhere I can rest without a pack of relatives prying around or confounding visitors <u>hanging on the bell</u>.</p> </entry>
